For the failed test: I think you can try use grpc_chttp2_hpack_compressor_set_max_table_size and update the max size to 2048, and change 114 to 57 to observe the same over flow effect. Because it is trying to overflow the decoder table, which defaults to 4096 < (114*(32+2+2)). Now that your array is only 64, the 65th header will likely fail to match the expect.

By reducing the header count to <64, you will not see this effect.

@yang-g Good catch, thanks!

BTW, the table size is further reduced to 1024, because otherwise verification would fail starting from i=33. This is related to the new ONE_ON_ADD_PROBABILITY being 32.
